$ Stellarium popup: Configuration -> Extras


{ Additional information settings

  Information settings that can be toggled are:
    • Use unit of measuremenat mag/arcsec² fur surface brighness
    • Use short notation for unit of measurement of surface brightness
    • Use formatting output for coordinates and time
    • Use designations for celestial coordinate systems

}
{ Additional buttons #stel-extras-additional-buttons

  Additional buttons that can be shown or hidden are:
    • Constellation boundaries button
    • Astermism lines button
    • Astermism labels button
    • Ecliptic grid button (there does not seem to be a default keyboard shortcut to show the ecliptic grid)
    • ICRS grid button
    • Galactic grid button
    • Centering button
    • Nightmode button
    • Nebula background button
    • Flib buttons
    • DSS button
    • HiPS button
    • Bookmarks button
    • Fullscreen button
    • Quit button
    • Buttons background

  These buttons are shown when the mouse is moved toward the bottom of the GUI
  of → Wissenschaft/Astronomie/tools/Stellarium.

}
